            "title": "Transocean Ltd. prices upsized public offering of 125M shares at $3.05 each, expecting approx $381.25M in gross proceeds.",
            "id": "ab292276-86e8-4fc4-a8ea-7079556abf8b",
            "description": "Steinhausen, Switzerland, Sept. 24, 2025 - Transocean Ltd. revealed that they have priced an underwritten public offering of 125,000,000 of their shares, having a par value of $0.10 each, at $3.05 per share. Initially planning to sell 100,000,000 shares, the company increased the offering size. The total gross proceeds from the transaction, before deducting underwriting discounts, commissions, and expenses, are anticipated to be around $381,250,000. All shares involved in the offering are from Transocean's own holdings. Moreover, Transocean has given the underwriters a 30-day option to buy up to 18,750,000 additional shares at the same offering price, barring underwriting discounts and commissions. The closure of the offering is scheduled for September 26, 2025, pending the fulfillment of standard closing criteria.",
